# 副簽

(pos:名詞)
<explanation>
yue:簽名嘅人其中一個，通常係主簽嘅助手或代表（量詞：個）
eng:Co-signer, a person who signs a document in addition to the main signer

<eg>
yue:貸款合同需要主簽同副簽都要簽名。 (dai4 kuen4 hon2 kei1 yiu1 zou4 sin1 same6 fu4 sin1 dou1 yiu1 sin1 ming4)
eng:The loan contract requires both the main signer and the co-signer to sign.

yue:公司嘅合約上，董事長係主簽，財務總監係副簽。 (seung1 yun4嘅 ho2 jok1 sang4, do4 ban4 zing4 jing1 係 zou4 sin1, fai4 wun4 zung1 gin4 係 fu4 sin1)
eng:On the company's contract, the Chairman is the main signer, and the CFO is the co-signer. [end of text]


